   189	
   190	**Validation plan.** GNSS-withheld replay of minutes-long LEO gaps (the test `SAFETY_CASE.md`
   191	§1.1 explicitly names): measure real revisit-gap statistics for the operating area/constellation
   192	mix, and the DR position-error growth vs truth across a gap, then set `t_dr` to the largest gap
   193	the drift budget tolerates inside the denied PL. Re-derive for any non-displacement hull.
   194	
   195	### 2.3 `t_eph` — `21600 s` (6 h ephemeris-age gate, G2e)
   196	
   197	**Derivation.** Directly from the baseline: SupGP maximum age provisional **6 hours**, anchored
   198	to the first supplied error-growth datum (~0.94 km orbit error at 6 h). The baseline states the
   199	orbit-error → navigation-integrity mapping is `[UNVERIFIED]` and the limit "shall be validated
   200	or tightened before steering trials." Proposed **21600 s**, matching the baseline unchanged.
   201	
   202	**Sensitivity.** 2× loose (12 h): SupGP orbit error grows to several km → range-rate prediction
   203	bias that the pass-nuisance state may not fully absorb → biased Doppler entering fusion. 2×
   204	tight (3 h): forces more frequent ephemeris refresh; if the at-sea fetch path is intermittent,
   205	over-age exclusion of otherwise-healthy satellites thins geometry and hurts availability.
   206	
   207	**Validation plan.** Propagate SupGP vs precise/near-real-time ephemerides to quantify the
   208	orbit-error → predicted-range-rate-error → navigation-integrity chain; tighten 6 h to the age
