     6	## What changed
     7	
     8	- Added workspace crate `pnt-tracker` with configurable-reference FFT correlation across
     9	  frequency bins and every circular time offset, followed by adjacent-sample phase-slope
    10	  refinement.
    11	- Added stateful block tracking that extrapolates measured drift to narrow the next search
    12	  but only emits a current-block measured peak.
    13	- Added typed `Detection`, `NoDetection`, and `TrackOutcome`. Threshold failure has no
    14	  envelope conversion and cannot fabricate an observation.
    15	- Added a constructor for v2/v4.1 `TrackerDoppler` envelopes. It requires UTC and a decimal
    16	  NORAD catalogue ID and reports correlation offset from nominal.
    17	- Added deterministic seeded PN/BPSK, frequency offset, linear ramp, circular delay, AWGN,
    18	  continuous-phase multi-block synthetic IQ and explicit noise-only simulator mode.
    19	- Documented the production reference plug-in point and real-sequence evidence boundary.
    20	
    21	## Numeric method and tolerance derivation
    22	
    23	The test fixture uses Fs = 8192 Hz, N = 256, and a 32 Hz coarse search grid. FFT circular
    24	correlation identifies delay at every frequency hypothesis. After unwinding the selected
    25	coarse frequency, the tracker aligns and despreads the samples and takes the argument of
    26	the sum of adjacent-sample conjugate products. Its residual-frequency estimate is
    27	`arg(sum(z[n] conj(z[n-1]))) Fs/(2 pi)`, so it is continuous rather than bin-quantised.
    28	
    29	The constant-offset and ramp tests use a conservative 4 Hz error bound (one eighth of the
    30	32 Hz coarse bin) at the tested high/moderate C/N0 values. For a linear ramp the adjacent
    31	phase products span samples 0 through N-1, so their analytic mean epoch is
    32	`block_start + (N-1)/(2 Fs)`. Ramp truth is evaluated at that midpoint. The injected
    33	75 Hz/s ramp moves 2.34375 Hz per 31.25 ms block; the adjacent-block smoothness bound is
    34	the analytic movement plus two independent 4 Hz measurement-error bounds (8 Hz residual
    35	error), excluding a coarse-bin/cycle-slip jump.
    36	
    37	The quality statistic is correlation peak power divided by the mean other-delay-bin power
    38	for the winning frequency hypothesis. The explicit default threshold is 32 (15.1 dB) to
    39	account provisionally for the multiple-cell frequency/delay search. Tests demonstrate zero
    40	false observations over 24 deterministic pure-noise blocks at that same threshold, followed
    41	by reacquisition, but do not establish a production probability of false alarm.
    42	
